P = 2π * √(a^3/mu)
n = 2π/P

thus n = 1/√(a^3/mu): n = √(mu/a^3)


M = n * t
M = E - e * sin E (ugh, soliving for E, no explicit solution)
Use Newton's method!
E_n+1 = E_n − (M−E+esinE) / (−1+ecos(E))
some good # of times

θ:
(1 - e) • tan^2(θ/2) = (1 + e) * tan^2(E/2)

θ = 2πn- 2i * tanh^(-1)((tan(E/2))/sqrt((e-1)/(e+1)))
r = [a(1 - e^2)] / (1 + ecosθ)